    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">MML (CC BY 4.0) &middot; D2L (CC BY-SA 4.0) &middot; 10 of 12</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">RNNs process sequences by maintaining hidden state. LSTMs add gates to control what to remember and forget. The hidden state is a <a href="https://june.kim/context-density"><img src="/reading/jk.png" alt="jk" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>lossy compression</a> of the past &mdash; the bottleneck that attention solves.</p>
    </div>

