    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">The scalar RNN above is pedagogical. Real RNNs use matrix multiplications: h<sub>t</sub> = tanh(W<sub>hh</sub> &middot; h<sub>t-1</sub> + W<sub>xh</sub> &middot; x<sub>t</sub> + b) where W<sub>hh</sub> is (hidden_dim &times; hidden_dim) and W<sub>xh</sub> is (hidden_dim &times; input_dim). GRUs are a simpler alternative to LSTMs with two gates instead of three.</p>

